# ✈️ Travel Planner

A web application that helps users organize and track places they want to visit. Users can add destinations, store travel notes, view live weather, and mark places as visited.

Built as a final project for WDD 330 — Web Frontend Development II.

---

## 🌍 Features

- **Add destinations** — save any city with a planned date and personal travel notes
- **View destination details** — see all info about a saved destination in one place
- **Mark as visited** — toggle destinations between "Planned" and "Visited"
- **Live weather** — current weather conditions via the OpenWeatherMap API
- **Search & filter** — search by city or country, filter by All / Planned / Visited
- **Persistent storage** — all data saved to localStorage so nothing is lost on refresh
- **Starter data** — pre-loaded with 5 example destinations from a local JSON file

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
travel-planner/
├── index.html          # Home page — destination list
├── add.html            # Add destination form
├── details.html        # Destination detail view
├── visited.html        # Visited destinations page
├── css/
│   └── styles.css      # All styles including animations
├── js/
│   ├── storageModule.js     # localStorage read/write operations
│   ├── displayModule.js     # Renders destination list and filters
│   ├── destinationModule.js # Handles the add destination form
│   ├── detailsModule.js     # Handles the details page
│   ├── visitedModule.js     # Handles the visited page
│   └── weatherModule.js     # Fetches live weather from OpenWeatherMap
└── data/
    └── destinations.json    # Starter destination data
```

---

## 💡 JavaScript Concepts Demonstrated

| Concept | Where Used |
|---|---|
| `localStorage` read/write/parse | `storageModule.js` |
| `async/await` | All modules |
| `try/catch` error handling | `storageModule.js`, `weatherModule.js` |
| Fetch API (external + cross-origin) | `weatherModule.js` |
| DOM manipulation | All modules |
| Higher-order functions `.map()` `.filter()` `.forEach()` | `displayModule.js`, `visitedModule.js` |
| Callbacks in event listeners | All modules |
| `this` keyword | All modules |
| Spread syntax `...` | `storageModule.js`, `destinationModule.js` |
| Closure / variable scope | `currentFilter` in `displayModule.js` |
| `setTimeout` | `destinationModule.js` |
| Form validation (client-side) | `destinationModule.js` |
| Template literals | `displayModule.js`, `visitedModule.js` |
| CSS Animations & Transitions | `styles.css` |
| URLSearchParams (Web API) | `detailsModule.js` |
| ES6 Modules / separation of concerns | All 6 JS files |

---

## 🔧 Data Sources

- **External API** — [OpenWeatherMap](https://openweathermap.org/api) for live weather data
- **localStorage** — stores all user-created destinations in the browser
- **Local JSON file** — `data/destinations.json` provides starter destination data on first load

---

## 🚀 How to Run

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/sil24040/W14-Final-portfolio-submission.git
```

2. Open the project in VS Code

3. Right-click `travel-planner/index.html` and select **"Open with Live Server"**

> No npm install or build step needed — this is a plain HTML/CSS/JS project.

---

## 🌤️ Weather API Setup

To enable live weather:

1. Sign up for a free API key at [openweathermap.org](https://openweathermap.org/api)
2. Open `js/weatherModule.js`
3. Replace `'YOUR_API_KEY_HERE'` with your key:

```javascript
API_KEY: 'your_actual_key_here',
```

> Note: New API keys take 10-15 minutes to activate after sign up.

